      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">How Scrabble AI Thinks</h2>

      <p>Understanding how AI evaluates positions helps you appreciate what optimal play looks like — and adopt similar thinking patterns in your own games.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 AI Decision Process</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Generate all legal moves:</span> The AI identifies every valid word placement on the current board using the rack tiles.</p></div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Score each option:</span> Calculate immediate points for every possible play (often thousands of options per turn).</p></div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Evaluate rack leave:</span> For each play, assess the quality of remaining tiles — how likely they are to produce good future plays.</p></div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Consider defense:</span> Factor in what scoring opportunities each play opens for the opponent.</p></div>
