      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Using AI for Training</h2>

      <p>AI opponents are the best available training tool because they play consistently, are always available, and you can analyze every decision they make.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Graduated difficulty:</span> Start at a level where you win 40-60% of games. This zone provides enough challenge to learn without demoralizing constant losses. Increase difficulty as your win rate improves.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Study AI moves:</span> After each game, review the AI's plays. When it finds words you missed, add those to your vocabulary. When it makes positional choices you did not expect, understand why — usually rack leave or defense.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Benchmark your progress:</span> Play a series of 20+ games at the same difficulty monthly. Track your average score and win rate over time. Improvement becomes clearly measurable.</p></div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 What AI Cannot Teach You</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">AI never plays phoneys, never bluffs, and never makes psychological plays. It also never gets tired or tilted. <span class="text-white font-medium">Human opponents test skills AI cannot</span> — reading bluffs, managing emotions after bad luck, and exploiting opponent weaknesses. Use AI for technical skills and humans for competitive skills.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Difficulty Levels Explained</h2>

      <p>AI difficulty settings typically work by limiting which words the AI considers or by occasionally choosing suboptimal plays. Understanding how each level works helps you select the right training partner.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🟢 Easy/Beginner AI</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Limited vocabulary (common words only). Does not prioritize premium squares. Makes suboptimal rack leave decisions. Good for beginners learning the game flow. Win rate for intermediate humans: 80-90%.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔴 Expert/Max AI</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Full dictionary knowledge. Perfect premium square targeting. Optimal rack leave evaluation. Defensive awareness. Effectively unbeatable over many games. Win rate for world champions: 30-40%.</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">AI vs Human — The Strategic Difference</h2>

      <p>The gap between AI and human play reveals exactly where humans have room to improve. Every point of difference represents a skill that can be developed.</p>

